    "body": "I think the `u` option given to `ar` [doesn't examine timestamps with sub-second accuracy](https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=blob;f=binutils/ar.c;h=117826d18e8b10079fdc01726641945e7e412ec1;hb=HEAD#l1365) and thus sometimes ignores the new object file.\n\n``` sh\necho 'extern crate foo; fn main() { println!(\"{}\", foo::foo()); }' > bar.rs\necho 'pub fn foo() -> int { 0 }' > foo.rs\nstrace -f -s 200 -e process -e open rustc foo.rs --crate-type lib\nstat libfoo.rlib\nrustc bar.rs -L .\n./bar\n\necho 'pub fn foo() -> int { 1 }' > foo.rs\nstrace -f -s 200 -e process -e open rustc foo.rs --crate-type lib\nstat libfoo.rlib\nrustc bar.rs -L .\n./bar\n\nsleep 1\nstrace -f -s 200 -e process -e open rustc foo.rs --crate-type lib\nstat libfoo.rlib\nrustc bar.rs -L .\n./bar\n```\n",
